<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880106-0117 </DOCNO><HL> Alliant Will Expand Its International Sales </HL><SO> </SO><CO> ALNT WNEWS </CO><DATELINE> LITTLETON, Mass.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Alliant Computer Systems Corp. said it will restructure its operations to expand international sales.    Separately, the maker of minisupercomputers for engineering and scientific applications said it named Roger Parsons, formerly president of VMark Inc., vice president, world-wide sales. Mr. Parsons succeeds David L. Micciche, who plans to take another position with Alliant after returning from a leave of absence, the company said.    As part of its restructuring, Alliant said it will cut about 40 positions from its headquarters operation while adding 50 new sales and marketing employees to its international operations. The changes will be made during the next 90 days, the company added. Alliant said it also has expanded its customer-support operations. </TEXT></DOC>